## Connection Management

### Client-Side

```
Connection Lifecycle:
  1. Authenticate via HTTP first (get session token)
  2. Connect to WebSocket with auth token
  3. Handle connection success -> join default rooms
  4. Handle reconnection automatically (with exponential backoff)
  5. Handle disconnect -> show offline indicator to user
  6. Clean up on page unload / app background
```

### Reconnection Strategy

```
Attempt 1:  wait 1 second       [DEFAULT] - all backoff values
Attempt 2:  wait 2 seconds
Attempt 3:  wait 4 seconds
Attempt 4:  wait 8 seconds
Attempt 5:  wait 16 seconds
Attempt 6+: wait 30 seconds (cap)

After [DEFAULT] 10 failed attempts: show persistent "Connection lost" banner with manual retry button
```

**Rules:**
- Always implement automatic reconnection - never require manual page refresh
- Show connection status to user (connected / reconnecting / disconnected)
- Queue outgoing commands during disconnect, send on reconnect
- Re-join rooms after reconnect
- Fetch missed events after reconnect (gap fill from REST API)

