## Delivering Updates to Offline Users

```
Pattern:
  1. Server event triggers an update
  2. Check if recipient is connected (has active socket)
  3. If online: deliver via WebSocket to user's personal room
  4. If offline: queue for delivery via another channel (push, email, etc.)
  5. On reconnect: client fetches missed events (gap-fill from REST API)
```

