## Error Handling

**Principle:** Define a finite set of error codes for real-time connections so clients can handle failures programmatically.

[REFERENCE] Common WebSocket/real-time error codes:

```
Server -> Client error events:
  {
    event: "error",
    data: {
      code: "VALIDATION_ERROR" | "PERMISSION_DENIED" | "RATE_LIMITED" | "INTERNAL_ERROR",
      text: "Human-readable error text",
      details: { ... }  // optional field-level errors
    }
  }

Client handling:
  - VALIDATION_ERROR: show inline error (e.g., "Payload exceeds allowed size")
  - PERMISSION_DENIED: show toast error
  - RATE_LIMITED: show cooldown indicator
  - INTERNAL_ERROR: show generic error toast
```

